# Analyze Apache projects using github stats

paragraphs.title: Get the list of Apache projects from github
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

import json
from urllib.request import Request, urlopen
apache_base_repos_url = "https://api.github.com/orgs/apache/repos"

repo_list_json = []

for page in range(1, 32):
    request = Request(apache_base_repos_url + "?page=" + str(page))
    # Add your github authentication token
    request.add_header('Authorization', 'token <your token here>')
    with urlopen(request) as url:
        repo_list_json.extend(json.loads(url.read().decode()))

paragraphs.title: Extract interesting data into a data frame
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

projects = []

for proj_num in range(1, len(repo_list_json)):
    project = repo_list_json[proj_num]
    project_description = {'name': project.get('name'), 'start_date': project.get('created_at'), 'forks': project.get('forks_count'), 'watchers': project.get('watchers_count'), 'size': project.get('size'), 'language': project.get('language')}
    projects.append(project_description)

project_df = sqlContext.createDataFrame(projects)
project_df.registerTempTable('projects')

paragraphs.title: Save the dataframe so we don't have to re-create it from github
Which Apache projects are watched the most?
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select name, watchers, forks, start_date, language, size 
from projects
order by watchers desc

paragraphs.title: Take a look at the watcher to fork ratio
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select name, watchers, forks, watchers / forks as watcher_fork_ratio, start_date, language, size 
from projects
order by watcher_fork_ratio desc
